<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-02-18T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-02-18T09:00:00-05:00" n="453" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d453">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.79661/2–1847: Telegram</note>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Smith</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-02-18T17:00:00+03:00">February
                                    18, 1947—5 p. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p rend="flushleft">434.</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                        <p>I also brought up matter of the lend-lease settlement, pointing out that
                            failure of the Soviet Govt to reply to our repeated overtures was <pb facs="0674" n="658" xml:id="pg_658"/> becoming embarrassing to us. I
                            stressed importance of beginning these discussions and continuing them,
                            even though they are protracted. Vyshinski<note n="1" xml:id="d453fn1">Andrey Yanuaryevich Vishinsky, Deputy Minister for Foreign Affairs
                                of the Soviet Union. This conversation probably occurred on February
                                15.</note> assured me that he would follow this through
                            personally.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>